                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-16T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1919, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April 17, 5.12 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2051. Confidential. For Ambassador Fletcher. In reply to your telegram of April
                    11th, 6 p.m., Cabrera expresses desire and willingness to cooperate but states
                    that in view of short time before new legislation may be enacted he considers it
                    not advisable at this time to press for provisional permits for new drilling.
                    However he will endeavor to obtain permission for building new tanks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
